<title>SOUTH AFRICA: TABLE- Hiveld half yr EPS rises, div steady.</title>
<headline>TABLE- Hiveld half yr EPS rises, div steady.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended June 30</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline		42.2	  vs 41.5</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 15.0	  vs 15.0</p>
<p>Analysts polled by Reuters forecast Hiveld's earnings in a 37.0-45.0 cents band with consensus at 39.0 cents. They expected a dividend of between 15.0 and 17.0 cents averaging at 15.7 cents.</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   40.70	 vs 39.30</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   30.70	 vs 41.01</p>
<p>    Tax			 10.00 gain  vs 1.71 charge</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   58.35	 vs 16.79</p>
<p>    Turnover		  1,599.88    vs 1,265.53</p>
<p>    Depreciation	    53.10	 vs 45.74</p>
<p>Div payable Oct 1</p>
<p>on register Sept 19</p>
<p>Full name: Highveld Steel and Vanadium Corp Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - Directors said that earnings for the full year are expected to show a real improvement over 1996 as divisions, including vanadium and steel, are seen performing well in the next six months. But ferro-silicon and medium carbon ferro-manganese are unlikely to be strong contributors, they said.</p>
<p>Shareholders were offered capitalisation shares in lieu of a dividend. The terms of the award will be announced on August 18.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
